cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of BDD in software development frameworks and proposes an ontology-based approach for automating the test of functional requirements of interactive systems.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper focuses on the assessment of interactive systems and mentions the flight tickets e-commerce domain as a case study.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes the use of an ontology to raise the abstraction level and support test automation.
- cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are less likely categories as they are not directly related to the topic of the paper.
